Grand, but . . .
Dec 2018
It's a long and winding path through Jordan's Furniture to the IMAX Theater, and only the first portion is truly well-marked. Of course the IMAX is there for promotional purposes, but . . . better signage along the way could only promote customer goodwill. The theater itself is grand and stadium-style with decent seat pitch (though the seats are no match for the increasingly common luxury models available in many venues), but notwithstanding Eliot Tatelman's on-screen claims that everything here is state of the art, the theater attendant's microphone was broken, and so she shouted, with limited success, about how to safely exit the theater after the show was over. That said, the massive screen image was crisp and impressive, and the "butt-kicker" speakers did just that.
Written December 29, 2018

Fun Theater Experience
Sep 2018 • Family
I hadn't been to this theater in years but decided to watch one of the releases of the Marvel movies over Labor Day Weekend. This place is hard to find! You have to go through almost the entire Jordan's Furniture store in order to get to the entrance. That being said, it's a lovely theater. They have real small popcorns that are a reasonable size. That alone gets them a star! The screen is curved so no matter where you sit you will get a nice view. This was 2D and a discount price since it was a special event but it looked like their prices were similar to other theaters for new releases and 3D. I'll definitely be returning!
Written September 20, 2018
